# Task 0 – High-Level Package Diagram

## Diagramme
```mermaid
graph TD
    %% Layers
    Presentation[Presentation Layer]
    BusinessLogic[Business Logic Layer]
    Persistence[Persistence Layer]

    %% Facade
    Facade[HBnB Facade (Unified interface)]

    %% Presentation Layer components
    subgraph "Presentation Layer"
        API[API / Endpoints (Controllers / Routes)]
        Services[Services (Request Handling)]
    end

    %% Business Logic Layer components
    subgraph "Business Logic Layer"
        DomainModels[Domain Models (User, Place, Review, Amenity) + Business Rules]
    end

    %% Persistence Layer components
    subgraph "Persistence Layer"
        Repositories[Repositories / Storage (Data access abstraction)]
        Database[Database (Persistent Storage)]
    end

    %% Communication
    Presentation -->|Calls Facade| Facade
    Facade --> BusinessLogic
    BusinessLogic -->|CRUD / Data operations| Persistence

    %% Detailed connections
    API --> Services
    Services --> Facade
    Facade --> DomainModels
    DomainModels --> Repositories
    Repositories --> Database

Notes

Presentation Layer : Gère les API et les services pour les interactions avec l’utilisateur.

Business Logic Layer : Contient les modèles de domaine et les règles métiers.

Persistence Layer : Responsable de l’accès aux données et de leur stockage.

HBnB Facade : Simplifie les interactions entre les couches Presentation et Business Logic.
